  "prompt": "I feel sad when?",
  "response": "Feeling sad can arise from a variety of situations or thoughts. People often feel sad when they experience loss, disappointment, loneliness, or unmet expectations. Reflecting on specific events, relationships, or changes in your life may help pinpoint when these feelings arise. It's also common to feel sad when you're overwhelmed, stressed, or when you're experiencing changes in your mood or environment.\n\nIf you're comfortable, consider talking about what might be making you feel this way. Sometimes sharing your feelings can provide clarity and relief. If you're looking for coping strategies or support, I'm here to help.",
